Package ohos.location

Class GeoAddress

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.location.GeoAddress
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public class GeoAddress
extends Object
implements Sequenceable
    Represents a data class that describes geographic locations.

    A geographic location consists of some parameters of an eXtensible Address Language (xAL) address, such as the longitude, latitude, country code, and administrative region name.

    Since:
    1

      • getDescriptions

        public String getDescriptions​(int index)
        Obtains the description identified by a specified index.

        Descriptions in the GeoAddress object are numbered from 0. The maximum number of descriptions is equal to the value set by getDescriptionsSize() minus 1. If the obtained index is smaller than 0 or greater than the maximum number, the value is null, indicating that no matching index has been found.

        Parameters:
        index - Specifies the index of the description, which must be greater than or equal to 0.
        Returns:
        Returns the description identified by the specified index. The value is null if no matching description exists.
        Since:
        1

      • setDescriptions

        public void setDescriptions​(int index,
                            String description)
                     throws IllegalArgumentException
        Sets the description identified by a specified index on the address list.

        Descriptions in the GeoAddress object are numbered from 0. You can modify a description identified by a specified index or append a description to the existing list. The index of the newly added description is equal to the number of descriptions obtained by getDescriptionsSize().

        Parameters:
        index - Specifies the index of the description. The value must be greater than or equal to 0 and less than or equal to the total number of descriptions obtained by getDescriptionsSize().
        description - Specifies a description. The value can be null if unknown.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Throws this exception if the specified index is smaller than 0 or greater than the total number of descriptions obtained by getDescriptionsSize().
        Since:
        1
